The evidence with the title 'Debunked: the myth that Ralph Nader cost Al Gore the 2000 Election ' says Nov 2, 2010  ... It 's really difficult to make the argument that Ralph Nader cost Al Gore the 2000 election , for multiple reasons.  ... Every 3rd party candidate got over 600 votes , which means that if any one of those 3rd party candidates had potentially dropped out and those votes had gone to Al Gore , he would have won too . 
